# Eval configuration — copy to .env and fill in:
#
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# promptfoo (the eval client) reads this file automatically on `npm run eval`.
# `npm run check` / `npm run index` are offline and need none of it.
#
# There is no gateway: promptfoo calls each provider DIRECTLY using that
# provider's API key below. Which models run is set in version-controlled YAML,
# not here:
#   • runner matrix → evals/promptfoo.base.yaml
#   • judges        → evals/judge-primary.yaml / evals/judge-secondary.yaml
# A provider's key only needs to be set if a model from that provider is listed.

# --- provider keys (set the ones your model list uses) ---
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=        # anthropic:messages:* runners + the primary judge
OPENAI_API_KEY=           # openai:chat:* runners + the secondary judge
# GOOGLE_API_KEY=         # google:* (Gemini / AI Studio) runners — optional
# AWS Bedrock (optional) — for bedrock:* runners. Static keys, or leave blank to
# use an IAM role / instance profile (AWS SDK default credential chain).
# AWS_SESSION_TOKEN is only for temporary (STS / SSO) credentials. Enable each
# model first in the Bedrock console → "Model access" for AWS_REGION_NAME, and
# install the SDK once: npm i -D @aws-sdk/client-bedrock-runtime
# AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=
# AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=
# AWS_SESSION_TOKEN=
# AWS_REGION_NAME=us-east-1

# Where promptfoo keeps its local store — the SQLite run history behind
# `npm run eval:view` plus the response cache. Pointing it at the repo (instead
# of the default ~/.promptfoo) keeps a clone self-contained and the history on
# one machine in one place. .promptfoo/ is gitignored. `npm run eval` defaults
# to this even if unset; set it here so `npm run eval:view` reads the same store.
PROMPTFOO_CONFIG_DIR=.promptfoo

# --- eval sampling + ship gate (scripts/gate.js) ---
# Each cell is sampled EVAL_SAMPLES times (promptfoo --repeat) so the gate judges
# a distribution, not one noisy judge score. The gate then requires the
# foundation column to clear an absolute quality floor AND beat its strongest
# baseline by a margin, both on the neutral (Opus) judge. `make eval` exits
# non-zero on a FAIL (override with `node scripts/eval.js --no-gate`). Defaults
# shown — raise EVAL_SAMPLES if cells come back noisy (large ±sd / WARN).
EVAL_SAMPLES=3
EVAL_MIN_QUALITY=0.7
EVAL_MIN_MARGIN=0.1
EVAL_MAX_STDEV=0.15
